1. Modules in Python allow you to organize
    and reuse code across multiple programs.

2. You can import built-in modules like math
    and internal modules which are available on
    https://pypi.org/   .

3. Use import module_name to bring a module into
    current script.

4. The pip tool is used to install and manage external
    Python packages.

5.  Use pip install package_name to add new packages
    your Python environment.